In .NET MAUI 10, Android defaults to **edge-to-edge** rendering, which changes how keyboard insets are handled. `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` is both deprecated (API 30+) and no longer effective in this mode.

**Two approaches:**

## 1. Use `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` (simplest)

Ensure your input is inside a `ScrollView` — MAUI's built-in keyboard auto-scroll (enabled by default) will adjust:

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*,Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ... />
    <ScrollView Grid.Row="1">
        <HorizontalStackLayout>
            <Entry Placeholder="Message..." HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
            <Button Text="Send" />
        </HorizontalStackLayout>
    </ScrollView>
</Grid>
```

## 2. Handle IME insets manually (more control)

In your `MainActivity.cs`, listen for keyboard insets and apply bottom padding:

```csharp
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.ApplicationModel;

// In MainActivity or a custom handler:
ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(
    Platform.CurrentActivity!.Window!.DecorView,
    new KeyboardInsetsListener());

class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        // imeInsets.Bottom gives keyboard height in px
        // Update your page's bottom padding via MessagingCenter or a shared service
        return ViewCompat.OnApplyWindowInsets(v, insets);
    }
}
```

## 3. Opt out of edge-to-edge (quick workaround)

In `MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);
    // Disable edge-to-edge, restoring .NET 9 behavior
    AndroidX.Core.View.WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window!, true);
    Window!.SetSoftInputMode(Android.Views.SoftInput.AdjustResize);
}
```

**Recommendation:** Option 3 is the fastest fix to restore .NET 9 behavior. For a polished chat UI long-term, option 2 gives you precise control over animations and padding when the keyboard appears.
